sentences.text:
They are not pressed by the respondent, leaving only the first two categories for consideration: 


 (a) PAYG payments totalling $9,516 received on behalf of the respondent by the applicant effectively on 14 August 2005; 

 (b) general interest charge credits arising from garnishee payments totalling $7,350 made by the respondent before the date of judgment but not credited to his account until after the date of judgment, resulting in an unquantified overcharge of general interest charges.

The applicant did not claim interest in the bankruptcy notice for the post-judgment period;

 (c) missed credits amounting to $31,007.72; and

 (d) a rounding credit of four cents.
